beer_description: Friend or foe? Sane or senseless? Harmless or harmful? Sometimes it takes awhile to get to know a stranger. Initial impressions are not always reality, so you must delve deeper. Beyond the initial floral hop aromas, malt sweetness is revealed, yet with a spicy undertone that exposes a very rye sense of humor. Take your time to get to know the Stranger. It's strangely satisfying.

Flemish-style red 100% fermentation rye whiskey barrels. 13 months in used American oak with proprietary blend of micro flora creating a brilliant deep ruby burgundy beer. Nose of cherries, vanilla and whiskey.

beer_description: RyePA is a "West Coast" style IPA brewed with rye malt, a great beer if you are a hophead.  This beer is brewed with 20% rye malt and 5% flaked rye, creating a big malty beer with a spice note and strong mouth feel.  The hops provide a full frontal assault of citrus, balancing quite well with the malt character.

Made once a year for San Francisco Beer week our Double Standard won silver at 2014 Double IPA Festival.  

Heavy weights of 2 row, Vienna, Acidulated and  Carahell malts and five different hops dry hopped twice give this beer it's hoppy hopped up alcohol punch.

A beer that truly started Samuel Adam's odyssey into extreme brewing. Its deep, full flavor explodes with notes of maple, vanilla, oak and toffee. This flavor, along with the rich mouth feel, has drawn comparisons to a vintage port, sherry, and cognac; and Samuel Adams Triple Bock should be enjoyed in much the same way. We recommend serving it at room temperature in a snifter a few ounces at a time - one bottle should generously serve two to three.  Its warming malt character and fruit esters make it an ideal after dinner aperitif.

There have been only three vintages produced: 1994, 1995 and 1997. 1994 and 1995 vintages are marked as such on the back label; 1997 vintage is not.

Named after the nautical term for the green buoy that helps navigate ships through the channels of Hampton Roads, the Green Can Gold Ale is a light-bodied Golden Ale. Crisp, clean easy drinking ale, our most approachable offering.

It is an ?Indian Pale ale? type of beer, with a harmonious balance between a marked bitterness (three types of hops are used to make it) and a pleasant fruitiness.  The HOUBLON CHOUFFE is unfiltered, and re-fermented in the bottle as well as in the keg.

Pull on your wool socks and crack open a 2? Below Ale. This tasty winter warmer started life as a small batch beer brewed for the Al Johnson Uphill Downhill a telemark ski race in Crested Butte, Colorado. The Uphill Downhill celebrates the exploits of Al Johnson, letter carrier extraordinaire, who delivered mail by ski in the late 1800's.

Winner of Samuel Adams 2010 Beer Lover?s Choice? campaign, this deep reddish-hued ale has a nice balance of sweet and spicy flavors. The slight roastiness and sweetness from the malt blend is complemented by pine and citrus notes from the combination of German and American hops. The defining ingredient in this ale, malted Rye, imparts additional complexity by delivering a spicy and slightly drying finish to this medium-bodied brew.

A group of hop-heads and publicans challenged our Beer Camp brewers to push the extremes of whole-cone hop brewing. The result is this: a 100 IBU, whole-cone hurricane of flavor. Simply put ?Hoptimum: the biggest whole-cone IPA we have ever produced. Aggressively hopped, dry-hopped, AND torpedoed with our exclusive new hop varieties for ultra-intense flavors and aromas.

Resinous ?new-school? and exclusive hop varieties carry the bold and aromatic nose. The flavor follows the aroma with layers of aggressive hoppiness, featuring notes of grapefruit rind, rose, lilac, cedar, and tropical fruit?all culminating in a dry and lasting finish.

Caf? Racer 15? features aromas of bright citrus and resinous pine from the generous use of Citra, Amarillo, Cascade and Chinook hops which are complimented by a dry malt finish. The result is a high revving Double IPA that is loud and assertive, much like the rebellious street racers who inspired it. Never ride alone...

Retrib?tion per Wiktionary: "punishment inflicted in the spirit of moral outrage or personal vengeance."

Well that pretty much sums it up, however to be a little more politically correct, you could just say "When life hands you lemons....make lemonade" Well I guess I traded in my lemons for a full silo of malted barley, a tasty stash of killer hops, some high quality California water and a healthy and continuous supply of brewers yeast. Blend these all together and throw in a little west coast brewing attitude and this wonderfully balanced Imperial IPA comes to life.

beer_description:
La Folie Wood-Aged Biere, is our original wood-conditioned beer, resting in French Oak barrels between one and three years before being bottled. Peter Bouckaert, came to us from Rodenbach home of the fabled sour red. Our La Folie emulates the spontaneous fermentation beers of Peter s beloved Flanders with sour apple notes, a dry effervescence, and earthy undertones. 

New in 2010, we'll do a single bottling of La Folie for the year. Collect the 22oz unique to 2010 designed bottle and start a yearly wood-aged collection of goodness.

Estil cerveser: ?BER ALE. Cervesa rossa d?alta fermentaci? adaptada a l?estil del nostre pa?s. Amb aquesta cervesa recuperem l?alta fermentaci? tradicional dels nostres avantpassats ibers. La recepta incorpora maltes i ll?pols emprats en l?elaboraci? de les cerveses de gran consum d?estil Pilsen (de baixa fermentaci?), o de la fam?lia de les Lager. 

Nota de tast: El gust dol? de la malta pilsen s?equilibra amb l?amargor del ll?pol i ?s ideal per fer passar la set. Temperatura de consum entre 4? i 8?C: a una temperatura baixa tenim els sabors i l?amargor del ll?pul clarament definits i, a m?s, resulta molt refrescant. La degustaci? ?ptima, per?, en una cervesa Ale s?aconsegueix per sobre dels 7?C, quan afloren les textures i sabors que produeix la fermentaci? del llevat Ale. 

Ingredients de la recepta: Aigua del Montseny. Maltes: pilsen, de blat i caramalt. Flor dels ll?pols: cascade, fuggles, nugget, target i celeia. Llevat.

beer_description: ?White Knuckle Ale? is a Double India Pale Ale. That?s right, twice the malt and twice the hops in one 14-barrel batch! It is named in honor of the exciting bike trail on Mt. Tam. If you are a ?hophead,? this one?s for YOU! It?s fat, chewy and resiny and pungent. Pour into a wide-mouthed glass and get ready to RIP! 8.0% alcohol by volume.

When we opened in 1989, the most adventurous beer in town was our Downtown After Dark Brown Ale. Our 22nd Anniversary Stout is a tribute to our roots and to those that dared to dream big in San Diego. Brewed with vanilla beans and aged three months in American oak bourbon barrels, this complex Imperial Stout has layers. Nuances of dark chocolate and espresso flavors are underpinned by hints of vanilla, bourbon, and oak. Save a bottle. Like us, this Special Release gets better with age.
